The greatest resistance is among the officers elected in the panel, suggesting that there are at least few bases or wishes for commitment in fiscal matters.
Galston foretells two phases in the battles between the Republicans of the White House and the Congress.
The first will happen next year in the form of party shocks, when the Republicans challenge Obama on the budget, taxes and medical assistance, followed by a period of increased bilateral cooperation.
What would cause the change?
Public opinion.
