EU changes rules for obtaining visas
People should visit the Visa Enquiries Service Centres before their interview in the Consular Section; the cost will be lower and as well as the waiting time.
With effect from 10 January 2011, the procedure for processing a visa will be changed in the United States Embassy and consulates.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants are required to visit the Visa Enquiries Service Centres (ASC) before their interview in the Consular Section.
The ASC staff will take the applicant's biometric information, which will be reviewed by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will have certain advantages for the applicants, including:
The total cost of processing the visa will be lower, no longer will be required to make a payment for the appointment, another payment for processing the visa application and more for the mail service to deliver the document.
The vacuum cleaner will only make a single payment that will cover the three services.
The current rate will remain unchanged: $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for visas on request (including visas for temporary workers) and $390 for traders and investors visas.
People who wish to renew their visa will not have to go to an interview with the Consular Officer, but they will only go to the nearest ASC where they will present their documents and take their marks.
Because biometric information will be taken into the ASC, applicants who require a second appointment to be interviewed in the Consular Section will remain at this time less than in the past.
Similarly, those applying for visas at the Consulates in Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and New Laredo will no longer pay the extra fee of $26.
For further information on the new visa application procedure, visit the following page http://mexico.usebassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
